        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian" anchor_text="Syphax">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="left_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>Numidaru[m] Rex: de quo multa Liuius.</marginalia_text>
                    <book title="Ab Urbe Condita"/>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>The king of the Numidians: much about whom in Livy.</translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="EN">
                <position place="left_margin" book_orientation="90">
                    <marginalia_text>Secrecy, on of [the] souerainest Rules, of Vegetius Rules: &amp; therfore more then once, of twise
                        repeatid, in that breife sententious chapter.
                  </marginalia_text>
                    <book title="De re Militari"/>
                </position>
            </language>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="left_margin" book_orientation="270">
                    <marginalia_text>Fons omniu[m] Strategematu[m], secretus, et intricatus procedendi modus, multis Technarum ambagibus implicitus.
                        Nam simplicia Strategemata rar&ograve; succedunt: Composita,
                        ipsos maxim&egrave; fallentes, fallu[n]t maxim&egrave;. Vulpis pera, dolis referta.
                    </marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>The source of all stratagems: a secret and complex way of proceeding, obscured by many ambiguities of 
            cunning tricks. For simple stratagems rarely succeed: composite ones deceive them greatly, they deceive greatly. The bag of the fox, stuffed with tricks. </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>Malo nodo, malus qua[e]rendus Cuneus.</marginalia_text>
                    <X-ref person="Jerome" book_title="Epistles"/>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>For a bad not, a bad wedge must be found.</translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="EN">
                <position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>Eueryman reddy to interteine intelligence, &amp; to mainteine discourse: but how few
                    meet, to reteine counsel, or to conceale matters of Secrecy?</marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
        </marginalia>
        
